LAGOS – Ace music maestro, Omotoyosi Kayode Iyun, popularly known as ‘Saint Janet’, will on Monday, June 13, 2022, entertain music lovers at the Academy Guest House, Agidingbi, Ikeja, Lagos. The special fiesta, meant to commemorate Nigeria’s Democracy Day, promises to be another exciting moment as fans of the controversial female Yoruba music sensation, ‘Saint Janet’ take the stage at the expansive Multi-purpose Hall of the Academy Guest House. In an interview with Daily Independent, Mr. Yomi Awo, Business Development Manager of Academy Guest House assured lovers of ‘Saint Janet’ of the special music of an exciting moment.“Adequate arrangements have been put in place to make the day one to remember for a long time for music lovers in Lagos and beyond on Monday to mark the democracy day. Academy Guest House otherwise called ‘House 5’ promises our guests exquisite moments of top-rated entertainment and accommodation. “We have ample space for parking, our expansive event hall is cosy, a 24-hour electricity supply is guaranteed and payment can be made at the venue,” Awo added. Awo disclosed that the Academy Guest House promoted and managed by Gateway Aviation Limited runs a 54-room, 8 executive and 36 standard accommodations, saying these also included 10 studio room apartments. He described a studio apartment as a self-contained breathing space that houses everything in a single room with a separate bathroom.